snippet.title: Celebrities With Herpes
snippet.description:
In this video, Alexandra Harbushka from Life With Herpes shares how common herpes really is by going down the list of A List celebrities who have oral herpes and genital herpes. This is not to downgrade them, but just showing you how many people actually have it. 


✅RESOURCES ✅

👉Not sure if you have herpes? Get a quick, confidential diagnosis here: http://bit.ly/herpalertdiagnosis (use promo code “lifewithherpes” to save 10%)

👉Already diagnosed with herpes and want step-by-step guidance on what to do next? Get the Herpes Outbreak Toolkit: http://bit.ly/lwhtoolkit 

👉Do you want to connect with other people who are living (and thriving) with herpes? Join our Secret Society: http://bit.ly/secretsocietylwh 

👉Do you need immediate 1-on-1 support? Schedule an emergency coaching call: http://bit.ly/lwhcall 

📚FREE EBOOKS 📚

📩Subscribe to my newsletter and download ‘9 Seldomly Used, But Incredibly Powerful Over The Counter Herpes Remedies’ and ‘The 5 Things I Wish I Had When I Was Diagnosed With Herpes’ here: http://bit.ly/LWHNewsletter 

💗ABOUT ALEXANDRA 💗

Alexandra Harbushka is the creator of Life With Herpes and she is on a mission to educate, entertain and connect with the underserved and often ostracized people living with herpes. Yes, Alexandra has herpes too and she totally gets what you are going through. She created this community so people living with herpes could learn, connect and get back to living their beautiful lives.

🔹Website: https://www.lifewithherpes.com/
🔹Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/alexandraharbushka/
🔹Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/lifewithherpespodcast
🔹Email: hi@lifewithherpes.com

Even our idolized celebrities have herpes too!

We idolize celebrities and think they walk on water. They're usually very attractive, hard working and have made it into the spotlight. Often times we forget that they’re human and yep they do all the things we do; the fart, they make mistakes and of course they have herpes too. 

Disclaimer: This video is NOT sponsored. Everything I discuss is based on my honest opinion and research. In full transparency, some links above may be affiliate links, which means I receive a small commission if you purchase the item through my link at no additional cost to you. Thank you for your support! XOXO Alexandra
